Mass spectroscopy (MS) was employed to identify the degradation pathways and reaction intermediates involved in TC•HCl degradation (Fig. 10
                        ). The MS of TC•HCl over NAB-4 reveals the possible structure of the intermediate degradation product. As the reaction proceeds, the TC•HCl molecule is gradually converted into small molecules from m/z = 445 to m/z = 218. Eventually, TC•HCl molecules are decomposed into small molecules such as H2O, CO2 and NH4+ 
                        [40] (Fig. 11
                        ).
